  <label>About</label>
  <row>
    <html>
      <article class="markdown-body">
        <h1>
          <a aria-hidden="true" class="anchor" href="#octopusdeploy-app-for-splunk" id="user-content-octopusdeploy-app-for-splunk">
            <span class="octicon octicon-link"></span>
          </a>OctopusDeploy App for Splunk</h1>

        <p>The OctopusDeploy App for Splunk provides a
          <a href="http://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/6.2.4/AdvancedDev/ModInputsIntro">modular input</a>
          to ingest data from an
          <a href="http://octopusdeploy.com/">Octopus Deploy</a>
          instance, and a set of dashboards and views to analyse the data.</p>

        <h2>
          <a aria-hidden="true" class="anchor" href="#installationconfiguration" id="user-content-installationconfiguration">
            <span class="octicon octicon-link"></span>
          </a>Installation/Configuration</h2>

        <p>The app makes use of the
          <a href="https://nodejs.org/">NodeJS</a>
          Splunk modular inputs.
        </p>

        <h3>
          <a aria-hidden="true" class="anchor" href="#prerequisites" id="user-content-prerequisites">
            <span class="octicon octicon-link"></span>
          </a>Prerequisites</h3>

        <ul>
          <li>Splunk Enterprise instance, version 6.2 or later.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>
          <a aria-hidden="true" class="anchor" href="#installing-nodejs-components" id="user-content-installing-nodejs-components">
            <span class="octicon octicon-link"></span>
          </a>Installing NodeJS components</h3>

        <ul>
          <li>Install the app</li>
          <li>
            Open a terminal window or command prompt, navigate to
            <code>$SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/octopus_deploy/bin/app</code>
          </li>
          <li>
            <code>npm install</code>
          </li>
          <li>Restart Splunk</li>
        </ul>

